    <item>
      <title>A novel suggestion regarding the Charm issue.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&amp;message.id=5147#M5147</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Replace the Coax spell with something else.&amp;nbsp; Or replace the 75 Charm.&amp;nbsp; One of the two.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The Devs have noted, with some good reasoning to back them up, that Charm could never go back to the way it was in POP days.&amp;nbsp; And I can understand the reason why charm was changed as harshly as it was.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But I can also say that these changes mean that Charm is now seldom worth doing at all except under rare circumstances.&amp;nbsp; And others have pointed out why this is so, I will not belabor the point.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Charm has, therefore, become a much-less-significant part of the enchanter arsenal.&amp;nbsp; And the Enchanter class needs some improvements.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Why compound the problem by giving us two new charms over five levels in TSS?&amp;nbsp; Each class is supposed to get the same number of spells in the new expansion, and Coax is taking up a spot that could be used for something that would solve&amp;nbsp;current problems, instead of exacerbating old ones.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Two charms per expansion has been the paradigm for Enchanters since the POP era, and Coax was obviously thrown in by the Autopilot while the Devs were thinking about something else.&amp;nbsp; Get rid of it.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
