    <item>
      <title>Crowd Control for Unmezzable Mobs: A Proposal</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&amp;message.id=5120#M5120</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'm not going to bore you all with a long preface or "state-of-the-class" type summary, so I'll just get right to it.&amp;nbsp; A proposal for enchanter crowd control for mobs that are normally unmezzable and/or unstunnable:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;cast on mob:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;"Daze" effect - 90% snare, 50% melee slow, -50% spell haste, attack debuff (or melee skill modifier decrease), duration&amp;nbsp;3 ticks&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;recourse on player (short duration window):&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;"Daze" effect recourse - fragile effect, with improved spell effect that recasts&amp;nbsp;an improved&amp;nbsp;"daze" spell on the player's target that has the same effect as the original but with a bonus to the resist modifier.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The basic premise of this effect is that the enchanter uses his or her magical control over the mind to disrupt the target creature's normal brain functions, significanly slowing its movement, attack rate, spellcasting, and making its attacks more wild and ineffective.&amp;nbsp; This is a short duration effect (3 ticks) that must be maintained by "concentration", which is enforced by the&amp;nbsp;having the auto-recast as a fragile effect.&amp;nbsp; If the enchanter breaks their concentration on&amp;nbsp;the hold they have over the creature's mind (by meleeing or spellcasting) they must either recast the daze&amp;nbsp;or deal with an extremely pissed off mob.&amp;nbsp; In order to prevent this from being used for kiting purposes, have the daze break when damaged (or possibly make a check to break each time it is damaged, like root).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This has the same risks of use as a mezmerize spell but the counterbalancing effect of having to "concentrate" to maintain the effect is that you can CC mobs that are normally unmezzable and/or unstunnable (e.g. giants).&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
