      <title>Wish list from the complainer</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&amp;message.id=5023#M5023</link>
      <description>If I'm gonna gripe all the time about the lousy state of enchanters, I might as well offer some solutions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1) Remove clarity potions from the game NOW. Putting crack in a bottle was the last insult and did wonders for making is even less necessary in a group. When I play my ranger, I'm appalled at the attitude toward getting an enchanter in the group. Just mooch the buffs and use a potion.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2) Refund Dire Charm and TD3 AAs and let us decide if we want to repurchase them or spend them elsewhere. Can you say &amp;quot;landslide?&amp;quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3) New AA: spell casting permanence. Every buffer class will want this, I suspect. With this AA, buff timers don't tick down as long as the caster is in the group. So long as the chanter stays in the group, his buffs will stay on. Requirement: SCRM.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4) More powerful nukes. I'm tired of druids and mages out-nuking me 3-4:1. Ancient:Neurosis is laughable.&lt;br&gt;4a) Nuke with a mana shatter. When the nuke lands, there is an x% chance that a chunk of the mob's mana will be destroyed, so they have less mana.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;5) Mana shatter: Instead of mana drain, this spell just plain wipes out a portion of a mob's mana pool and dispells it. Useful for those high caster mobs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;6) Better DoTs. Shammies can do 2k/tick. We do what? 300? In particular, Asphyxiate has the nice extra feature of dropping the mobs Str.  A new DoT that does more damage, lowers str/atk/dex/agi, would be a big improvement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;7) New AA: Weakening Hold. One or two seconds before charm breaks, the chanter gets the message &amp;quot;You feel your grip over %t weakening,&amp;quot; giving them a start on recharming. Requirement: Dunno, maybe TD3.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;8) Mental balance. Just like the cleric AA divine arbitration balances HP, let us balance out the mana in a group, excluding the pure melees. So if a cleric is going OOM and the SK and chanter are 90 mana, it refills the cleric.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;9) Improved cripple. Why do chanters and shammies have the exact same cripple? Shammies get the better slow, ever so slightly. We should get a better cripple.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;10) More stunnable mobs. Man, I'm sick of mobs resisting stuns. Diodites, anyone?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;11) A better epic effect. Our epic click is a joke.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;12) Why is Hastened Gathering a 2-2-2 AA while Quick buff and hastened MGB are 3-6-9?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;13) Silent Casting should not be activated, it should be innate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Have at it, boys and girls.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
