      <title>Long time coming</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&amp;message.id=5022#M5022</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Well it has been a long 5 + years for me as an enchanter,but I believe the time has come for me to allow my toon to die one final time and move on.I have been patient to no end in waiting for the changes needed to bring us back to being something other than a buffbot and it obviously isnt coming.I have seen the highs and lows to being a chanter,and these days unless I am raiding,a group cannot be found.I have tried to start groups,tried to join all guild groups,and the response is always the same - enchanters are not useful enough in todays content to provide a modicum of dps to help groups.Against raid targets we vary but roughly we can sustain around 200-300 dps while other classes snicker while they crank out 1.2-1.6k dps against the same targets.Against group targets we fair even worse,with many of the mobs being dead before we can actually land more than 1 nuke.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Instead of the devs showing notice to the pleas of the enchanter community to restore charm to a useful state once more,they instead offer us somewhat sub par spells that help others - help others in doing more dps,help others in regening more mana.We asked for an inherent spell or ability to regen our own mana and are instead given an aura to help those in group - proof yet again we are meant to do nothing more than help others while remaining essentially useless by ourselves.If we generate a ceratain degree of hate in a mob,the enchanter is still high on that mobs target list if the tank goes down - and yet our ability to mitigate damage or survive against the increasingly difficult mobs has not scaled upwards.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;On the solo abilities,enchanters fair by far among the worst now that charm has been crippled to uselessness.Charm was crippled when other classes complained we could sustain roughly 1k dps with certain charmed pets.An ability at that time that was not reached by those classes.Now those same classes far surpass what we were capable of in the past,yet we remain with a nerf to keep us in check.On days when I am not raiding,I have to bear listening to how beastlords,necros,wizards,bards,mages,can solo areas like RSS when they cant find groups,and I wonder why I am listening to their chat while sitting in the guild pool.Because I cant find or make a group - people are no longer interested in having an enchanter along now that content has been made more friendly towards non cc groups.DoD offered a degree of hope for us like PoR did,yet with DoD,almost all single group missions were designed so poorly,and in such difficulty,that no one wants to repeat them.Our hopes of attaining all our spells from that expansion rested solely on our abilities to be first in line to buy it and start on it asap.After the first few weeks of release,no one wanted to repeat the missions needed for spells or disciplines,thus leaving many in the dark for attaining what they needed.PoR was worse on this note in that groups wanted heavy dps to help them get through content and we = not heavy dps.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My subscription runs out in first week of June and I doubt seriously I will renew anymore because we have been handed too many empty promises.An enchanter is what I started with and have no desire to start another class this late in the game.I have managed to rise in power to the point I am in the top 10 on my server,yet this class has long since been fun to play and impossible to solo effectively when we cant find groups.I have tried to lend my voice on opinions and suggestions for our class,and have watched as we are ignored from one expansion to the next or tossed small bones in order to pacify us into submission.We have recieved no compensation for the nerf given to us when charm was crippled,and have been laughed at by the devs when we tell them we have several thousand suggestions for them to look at for a fix.We ask for our abilities to be restored and are ignored,necros ask for the ability to crank out more dps and are given more spells to help them.Bards ask for more abilities to make them even more useful in groups and ask for better abilities to solo and are handed those on a silver platter.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I for one have had enough.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
