    <item>
      <title>Mind Shatter: Adjustments?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&amp;message.id=4954#M4954</link>
      <description>There's been a lot of chatter about Mind Shatter in various forums, so I thought I'd get a post in here to centralize discussion a bit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Right now, this spell is a very efficient DoT and situational mana regen spell for targets that have Mana to tap, but is uncastable on mana-less targets.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;While, obviously, in an ideal world, this spell would work on all targets, I don't think that change is likely to occur.   The other possible thing we can push for is for the spell to be castable, as a DoT, on targets with no mana, but that it would not return the mana regen recourse, making it an inefficient but still significant short term DPS boost when combined with nuking (The damage per cast time on Mind Shatter is fairly high.).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Please weigh in on what, if anything, you feel we should try to get done with this spell.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;My personal stance is that the spell is fine as is because I would virtually never use it in situations where it didn't return the recourse, so I'd rather use my/our finite collective effort on other issues, but if folks feel that pushing one or the other of the alternatives is important, we can go with that.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
